         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:knoll1996"/><citedRange>41</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">if this age also comes to others</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Ob dieses Alter auch anderen kommt?</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Does this age come onto others as well?</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>75</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">if this was a rich or a poor being ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1967a"/><citedRange>67</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b7"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1954"/><citedRange>738</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:knoll1996"/><citedRange>43, 47</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">not even able to speak, he respires only with difficulty</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="parallels">MaitrHami 13, 3</note><note type="philcomment">This fragment contains part of the thirteenth act of the Maitreyasamitināṭaka; an Uy. parallel would be MaitrHami 13, 3, which, unfortunately, is missing. See also <bibl><title corresp="ref:pinault1999"/><citedRange>201</citedRange></bibl>.</note><note type="remarks">Fragment of a manuscript which includes A 251 - A 294 (cf. <bibl><title corresp="ref:gengetal2004a"/><citedRange>64-65</citedRange></bibl>). Lines a8 and b1 are lost.</note></p>
         </div>
